---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import RegisterInterestForm from "../components/RegisterInterestForm.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <header>
    <h1>Domain Exams</h1>
    <p><strong>Written, proof-based exams for serious self-study in math and CS.</strong></p>
    <p><a href="#register-interest">Register Exam Interest</a></p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>The Vision</h2>
    <blockquote class="vision-quote">
      <p>
        “Free education is abundant, all over the Internet. It’s the desire to learn that’s scarce.”
      </p>
      <footer>— Naval Ravikant</footer>
    </blockquote>
    <p>
      Textbooks are cheap, courses are everywhere, and AI tutors are free. Access to knowledge is no
      longer the bottleneck. Validation is. There is no widely recognized way to demonstrate mastery
      of a subject—no matter how seriously it was studied. Domain Exams fills that gap by providing
      a durable, credible mark of achievement.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What Domain Exams Are</h2>
    <p>
      Domain Exams are written examinations that assess mastery of undergraduate-level material in
      mathematics and theoretical computer science. They emphasize correct reasoning and proof-based
      justification, with clearly defined scope and standards.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Written and proof-based</strong> — not multiple choice.</li>
      <li><strong>Standards, not ranking</strong> — results reflect absolute performance.</li>
      <li><strong>Depth over breadth</strong> — each exam is narrow but rigorous.</li>
      <li><strong>Reasoning-first</strong> — understanding over memorization.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Exams</h2>
    <style>
      .exam-icon {
        width: 1.5em;
        height: 1.5em;
        vertical-align: middle;
        margin-right: 0.5em;
        display: inline-block;
      }
    </style>
    <h3>
      <a href="/exams/discrete-mathematics">
        <img src="/assets/discrete-mathematics.svg" alt="" class="exam-icon" />
        Discrete Mathematics
      </a>
    </h3>
    <h3>
      <a href="/exams/algorithms">
        <img src="/assets/algorithms.svg" alt="" class="exam-icon" />
        Algorithms and Data Structures
      </a>
    </h3>
    <p>
      Additional exams are in development. <a href="#register-interest">Register interest</a> in the subject
      of your choice.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Why Participate</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Demonstrate honors-level undergraduate understanding.</li>
      <li>Turn self-study into a clear, external objective.</li>
      <li>Earn an independent, durable signal of mastery.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What You Receive</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        A result of
        <strong>Mastery</strong>,
        <strong>Proficiency</strong>,
        <strong>Partial</strong>, or
        <strong>Insufficient</strong>.
      </li>
      <li>
        A printed certificate for outcomes of <strong>Mastery</strong> or <strong>
          Proficiency
        </strong>.
      </li>
      <li>A shareable result page under an unguessable URL (not indexed).</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="register-interest">
    <h2>Register Interest</h2>
    <p>Email and subject selection are required; all other fields are optional.</p>
    <RegisterInterestForm />
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .vision-quote {
    margin: 14px 0;
    padding-left: 14px;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--hairline);
    max-width: var(--text-width);
  }

  .vision-quote p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .vision-quote footer {
    margin-top: 0px;
  }
</style>
